        "discriminators": [
          "The whole movement, not just the escapement: winding a mainspring (a fast ratcheting click train), the gear train whirring, the pendulum, cuckoo mechanics. Denser and less regular than CLOCKS-TICK, and almost entirely high-frequency - a clock movement is tiny, so it has essentially no low-band energy, which is the strongest cue here.",
          "Against CLOCKS-TICK: a tick is one sparse periodic impulse per second; MECHANICS is many overlapping small events with a lower onset_periodicity.",
          "Against MECHANICAL-GEARS: UCS routes small clock gears here and big ones there. That is a size call - but size shows up as low_band_energy, so it is at least partly measurable.",
          "Against MECHANICAL-RATCHET: winding IS a ratchet. Text decides."
        ],
